---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "How long should I wait to respond to an initial job offer?",
    a: "It's best to acknowledge the offer immediately, expressing gratitude and enthusiasm, and ask for a specific timeframe (usually 2-3 business days) to review the details before providing a formal response."
  },
  {
    q: "Is it okay to negotiate over email?",
    a: "Yes! Negotiating over email allows you to carefully draft your points, reference market data clearly, and removes the pressure of thinking on your feet during a phone call. It also provides a written record of the negotiation."
  },
  {
    q: "What if the company says they don't negotiate?",
    a: "If a company states they don't negotiate on base salary, you can try negotiating other aspects of the compensation package, such as a signing bonus, extra paid time off, flexible work hours, or an earlier performance review."
  },
  {
    q: "Should I disclose my current salary during negotiations?",
    a: "Generally, no. Your value to the new company is based on the role and current market rates, not your previous compensation. Focus the conversation on market research from sites like Glassdoor and Levels.fyi."
  },
  {
    q: "What is the 'power of silence' in negotiations?",
    a: "The power of silence means that after you state your counter-offer or make a request, you should stop talking (or writing). Wait for their response rather than rushing to fill the silence or negotiating against yourself."
  }
];

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": f.a
      }
    }))
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout
  site="getthebag"
  title="15 Salary Negotiation Email Templates"
  description="Master your salary negotiation with these 15 copy-paste email templates covering counter-offers, raises, remote work, and more."
  canonical="https://getthebag.photonbuilder.com/salary-negotiation-emails"
  schema={JSON.stringify(schema)}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>15 Salary Negotiation Email Templates</h1>
      <p>Use these copy-paste templates to navigate initial offers, counter-offers, promotions, and more.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Essential Negotiation Principles</h2>

      <h3>The Research Phase</h3>
      <p>Before sending any negotiation email, you must know your market value. Utilize platforms like <strong>Glassdoor</strong>, <strong>Levels.fyi</strong>, and <strong>Payscale</strong> to gather data on what professionals with your experience level and skill set are making in your geographic area.</p>

      <h3>Timing Strategy</h3>
      <p>Always respond to an initial offer quickly to express excitement, but ask for time to review. When sending a counter-offer, send it within 24-48 hours of receiving the official written offer. Do not delay too long, as it can signal disinterest.</p>

      <h3>The "Never Negotiate Against Yourself" Rule</h3>
      <p>Once you send your counter-offer or make a request, wait for their response. Do not follow up immediately with a lower number if they take a day or two to reply. Stand firm and let the process unfold.</p>

      <h3>The Power of Silence</h3>
      <p>In both verbal and written negotiations, state your case and then pause. The silence might feel uncomfortable, but it often prompts the other party to make concessions or explain their constraints, giving you valuable information.</p>

      <h3>Gender Pay Gap Negotiation Tips</h3>
      <p>Studies show women are penalized more often than men for negotiating. To mitigate this bias, frame your request as a mutual benefit (e.g., "I want to ensure we're aligned so I can hit the ground running"). Rely heavily on objective market data rather than personal needs, and practice adopting a collaborative, problem-solving tone.</p>

      <h2>15 Salary Negotiation Email Templates</h2>

      <div>
        <h3>1. Initial Offer Response (Asking for Time)</h3>
        <p>Use this immediately after receiving the verbal or written offer.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you so much for the offer for the [Job Title] position! I am thrilled about the opportunity to join the team and contribute to [Company Goal/Project].

Could I have until [Day of week, e.g., Wednesday] to review the offer details thoroughly?

Best regards,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>2. Counter-Offer Email (Base Salary)</h3>
        <p>A standard template for negotiating a higher base salary.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you again for the offer. I am very excited about the prospect of joining [Company Name].

After reviewing the package, I would like to discuss the base salary. Given my [X] years of experience in [Skill/Industry] and the market data for similar roles in [City/Area], I was hoping we could explore a base salary of [Target Salary].

I am confident that I can bring significant value to the team and would love to reach an agreement.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>3. Competing Offer Leverage (Match)</h3>
        <p>When you have another offer but prefer this company.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

I am very excited about the offer to join [Company Name]. However, I want to be transparent that I have received another offer from a different company for [Competing Salary].

[Company Name] remains my top choice, and I would love to sign with you. Would you be able to match this base salary of [Competing Salary]?

Looking forward to your thoughts.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>4. Promotion Request Email</h3>
        <p>To request a promotion after significant achievements.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Manager's Name],

I hope you're having a good week. I'd love to schedule some time to discuss my career progression. Over the past [Time Period], I've taken on [New Responsibility 1] and successfully completed [Major Project], resulting in [Quantifiable Result].

Given my increased scope of work, I'd like to discuss the possibility of transitioning into a [Target Job Title] role. Let me know when you might have 30 minutes to chat.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>5. Raise Request (Annual Review)</h3>
        <p>Setting the stage for a salary increase during performance reviews.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Manager's Name],

As we approach our upcoming performance review, I would like to include a discussion about my compensation.

Since my last review, I have accomplished [Achievement 1] and [Achievement 2], which have contributed to [Business Impact]. Based on these contributions and current market research for my role, I am hoping to discuss a salary adjustment to [Target Salary].

I look forward to our conversation!

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>6. Remote Work Negotiation</h3>
        <p>If salary is fixed, negotiate work flexibility.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you for confirming the salary details. I understand the constraints around the base compensation.

Since the salary is fixed, would you be open to a flexible work arrangement? I would love to propose working remotely [X] days a week. I have a proven track record of productivity in a remote setting and believe this would make the overall package work for me.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>7. Signing Bonus Request</h3>
        <p>A great alternative when base salary is non-negotiable.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

I completely understand that the base salary of [Amount] is the maximum for this role.

Given the value I bring and the potential cost of leaving my current annual bonus at my previous employer, would [Company Name] be open to offering a one-time signing bonus of [Amount]?

If we can agree on this, I am ready to sign the offer today.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>8. Start Date Negotiation</h3>
        <p>To ask for more time before starting.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you for the updated offer. I am very eager to get started!

Regarding the start date of [Proposed Date], I was hoping we could push it back to [New Date]. This will allow me to wrap up my current projects smoothly and take a short break to ensure I hit the ground running at [Company Name].

Would [New Date] work for the team?

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>9. Benefits Negotiation</h3>
        <p>To negotiate additional Paid Time Off (PTO).</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you for sending over the benefits package. While the base salary aligns with my expectations, I noticed the PTO allowance is lower than what I currently receive.

Would it be possible to increase the paid time off to [X] days per year? This adjustment would make the overall package highly competitive for me.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>10. Declining Respectfully</h3>
        <p>When the offer isn't right, keep the door open.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you so much for the offer to join [Company Name]. I greatly enjoyed meeting the team and learning about the exciting projects ahead.

After careful consideration, I have decided to decline the offer at this time. It was a difficult decision, but I have accepted an opportunity that aligns more closely with my current career goals.

I wish you and the team the best of luck and hope our paths cross again in the future.

Warm regards,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>11. Counter-Offer Email (Below Market Value)</h3>
        <p>When the initial offer is significantly lower than average.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you for the offer. I'm very enthusiastic about the [Role] position.

I was surprised by the base salary of [Amount], as my research on Glassdoor and Levels.fyi indicates that the market average for this level of experience in our area is closer to [Market Amount].

Could we discuss adjusting the base salary to better align with the market rate?

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>12. Competing Offer Leverage (Beat)</h3>
        <p>When you want your top choice to beat a higher competing offer.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

I am very excited about the possibility of joining your team. I want to let you know that I have another offer on the table for [Competing Salary].

[Company Name] is my preferred choice because of [Reason]. If you are able to increase the base salary to [Target Salary], I would be thrilled to accept your offer immediately.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>13. Ask for Early Review</h3>
        <p>In lieu of an immediate raise, negotiate an accelerated review.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

I understand the budget for this role is strict right now. If we proceed with the current base salary, would you be open to scheduling a formal performance and compensation review in 6 months instead of 12?

This would give me the opportunity to prove my value and align my compensation with my contributions sooner.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>14. Equity/Stock Options Negotiation</h3>
        <p>To negotiate more equity if salary is capped.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

Thank you for clarifying the constraints on the base salary.

Since I am highly invested in the long-term success of [Company Name], would it be possible to increase the equity grant to [Amount/Percentage]? I believe this would be a great way to align my compensation with the company's growth.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>15. Follow-Up After No Response</h3>
        <p>When they haven't replied to your counter-offer.</p>
        <pre><code>Hi [Name],

I hope you're having a great week!

I just wanted to follow up on my previous email regarding the offer for the [Role] position. Please let me know if you need any additional information from me or if there is a good time to briefly discuss it on a call.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Best,
[Your Name]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div>
        {faqs.map(f => (
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>{f.q}</h3>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
  .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 650px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.5; }

  .content-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .content-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .content-section p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .faq-item { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .faq-item h3 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .faq-item p { margin-bottom: 0; }
</style>
